Higher pair (Aces) beats lower pair, if both players have the same pair the highest other card wins. In this case the Aces beat the Kings and the Queens beat the Tens. The kicker, the highest odd card, is used to separate further equal hands, so 7s beats 2s, 6s beats 5s and 4s.

The best hand a player can get is thus AA KK QQ JJ. But there are no A, J, Q, K in the hole cards and no J, Q, K, or A in community cards, so no Straight Flush or Royal Flush is possible. This leaves us with Full House or better, that can be formed:
- Big slick (A-K)
- Four of a kind (8s)
- Full house (9s over 5s)
- Straight (4-6)
